goals.question: What is the distribution of module dependencies?
goals.visualization: Histogram of the number of dependencies per module
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of dependencies across modules and identify any outliers.

goals.question: Which module has the highest number of dependencies?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of the top 10 modules with the highest number of dependencies
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the modules that are critical to the project and may require more attention.

goals.question: What is the correlation between the number of dependencies and the module size?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of module size vs number of dependencies
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is a relationship between module size and the number of dependencies, which can help us optimize the project structure.

goals.question: What is the average number of dependencies per module?
goals.visualization: Box plot of the distribution of number of dependencies per module
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the central tendency and spread of the number of dependencies per module.

goals.question: What is the most common dependency pattern between modules?
goals.visualization: Sankey diagram of the most common dependency patterns between modules
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the flow of dependencies between modules and identify any recurring patterns.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['source'].value_counts(), bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(x=data['source'].value_counts().mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(x=data['source'].value_counts().median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.xlabel('Number of dependencies per module')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of module dependencies?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    top_10 = data.groupby('source').count().sort_values(by='target', ascending=False).head(10)
    ax = top_10.plot(kind='bar', y='target', legend=False)
    ax.axhline(y=top_10['target'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max value: {:.2f}'.format(top_10['target'].max()))
    ax.set_xlabel('Module ID')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Dependencies')
    ax.set_title('Which module has the highest number of dependencies?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
